YENAGOA – The Minister of State for Petroleum Re­sources, Timipre Sylva, has disclosed that arrangements have been conclud­ed for the Brass Fertilizer Petrochemi­cal Company Limited (BFPCL) Project, Brass Island, Bayelsa State, to access Foreign Direct Investment (FDI) by the end of 2020. Sylva also said that plans were being fine-tuned for the establishment of the Atlantic Modular Refinery and a fuel depot on the Brass Island. He stated these in his remarks during a grand reception organised in his honour by the people and monarch of Okpoama Kingdom, King Ebitimi Banigo, at the Okpo Square in Okpoa­ma in the Brass Local Government Area of the state. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! It would be recalled that in December 2016, the BFPCL signed a $6bn off take deal with BP Oil International Limited for the first phase of the project. The contract, which was signed at the London office of BP Oil Internation­al Limited, was for exclusive off take of methanol production for the phase one of the BFPCL project. Zulum Offers Christmas Largesse To Soldiers Of 151 Battalion Jigawa Pays Over N19bn Pension Dues In Five Years The minister, who highlighted criti­cal investments on the Brass Island that would bring about huge economic op­portunities to the Niger Delta, called on the people of the area to always ensure a peaceful environment for businesses to thrive. Sylva, who is a son of Okpoama, said, “This community is at the verge of something great, and I can tell you that for free. Today, we have put fin­ishing touches to the Brass fertilizer project. We are going to take the FDI at the end of this year, which is already with us.” SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION